@aaugustin You are correct, the version 2 refactor added all those exceptions and I was unaware at the time that that format for adding information to exceptions had been deprecated.

@SavinaRoja I see that the link that you have provided does include information on using `six.reraise()` to allow for raising an exception in a manner that functions properly in both Python 2.x and 3.x

I have found that future includes `raise_with_traceback`, which can be used in both python 2 and 3 to get us where we want, so I will be updating all of the exceptions to use that to allow the library to live for those using the new hotness like @aaugustin, and those like me that are stuck in the dark ages of 2.x for a little while longer.

@aklatt1194 agreed it would be nice be flexible about that. It's pretty trivial for transmute-core to provide some sort of response object to allow that customization:

```
import transmute_core

def foo():
    return transmute_core.response({}, status=201)
```

And then handles that appropriately in the method. However, the tricky aspect comes in on the autodocumentation.

We need to document the behavioral change in the swagger spec. There's an object of <status_code, response_type> pairs that is dictated in an API spec:

https://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/master/versions/2.0.md#paths-object-example

It would be great for the API to be documented there as well.

To do that, I could imagine another annotation in describe:

```
@describe(..., status_code=201)
def foo():
    return {}
```

But I'm wondering if there's some way to document multiple different response types, of different schemas, without requiring explicit declarations all over the place:

```
@describe(response_type_by_code={200: ModelA(), 201: ModelB()})
```

Thoughts?

Something like this should work.  You would need to add the CSS to `mkdocs.yml` via `extra_css` as Python Markdown doesn't recognize `link` tags.

```js
<script src="https://cdn.rawgit.com/knsv/mermaid/7.0.0/dist/mermaid.min.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript">
(function (document) {
    var convertUML = function(className, settings) {
        var charts = document.querySelectorAll("pre." + className),
            arr = [],
            i, j, maxItem, diagaram, text, curNode;

        // Is there a settings object?
        if (settings === void 0) {
            settings = {};
        }

        // Make sure we are dealing with an array
        for(i = 0, maxItem = charts.length; i < maxItem; i++) arr.push(charts[i]);

        // Find the UML source element and get the text
        for (i = 0, maxItem = arr.length; i < maxItem; i++) {
            childEl = arr[i].firstChild;
            parentEl = childEl.parentNode;
            text = "";
            for (j = 0; j < childEl.childNodes.length; j++) {
                curNode = childEl.childNodes[j];
                whitespace = /^\s*$/;
                if (curNode.nodeName === "#text" && !(whitespace.test(curNode.nodeValue))) {
                    text = curNode.nodeValue;
                    break;
                }
            }

            // Do UML conversion and replace source
            el = document.createElement('div');
            el.className = className;
            parentEl.parentNode.insertBefore(el, parentEl);
            parentEl.parentNode.removeChild(parentEl);
            mermaid.mermaidAPI.initialize(settings);
            console.log(mermaid.mermaidAPI.getConfig());
            var insertSvg = function(svgCode) {
                el.innerHTML = svgCode;
            };

            mermaid.mermaidAPI.render(className + '-' + i.toString(), text, insertSvg);
        }
    };

    function onReady(fn) {
        if (document.addEventListener) {
            document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', fn);
        } else {
            document.attachEvent('onreadystatechange', function() {
                if (document.readyState === 'interactive')
                    fn();
            });
        }
    }

    onReady(function(){
        var config = {logLevel: 4, startOnLoad: false};
        convertUML('uml-flowchart', config);
        convertUML('uml-sequence-diagram', config);
    });
})(document);
</script>
```

