@christianmemije @rtibbles 
A score seems like something that naturally pops up only after completion. Otherwise, how can you be scored on something you haven't submitted? Even if we calculate score in real time, if answers are changed by the learner while test-taking, we'll always have this fluctuating number that is mixed with scores of those who have completed the exam. 

I would opt for either a fixed 0% for in-progress learners or not display a score at all. That way it's easier to visually distinguish those who have completed vs in progress

@indirectlylit I have simplified the logic to only use `synced` now.

I think the reason I led myself astray was because I was trying to allow for situations where the Collection was synced, but one of its constituent models was not (but also to be wary of the circumstance where the Collection had no models, because it was not yet synced).

I think the getter/setter `synced` for Collections with an internal `_synced` property solves this most neatly.

